<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub142.ezboard.com/feqdivabardsofeverquestfrm2.showMessage?topicID=797.topic" target="top">The power of the DS</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<br>
Essentially, use a DS for unslowable mobs like Vindi, but the 5pt DS you have will create more probs than it helps.<br>
<br>
A small raid with average lvl of 62 can get 166 pt DS on a tank.  Against a high end mob that can add up to around 450 dps.  The easy way to look at it is 1 pt DS equals 300 dmg against a Vindi-type mob.  Not chicken feed.  But no wizzies involved in that ds.  Its potion, mage and bard. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=444932" target="top">My bitchin' gear</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tiane>Tiane</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/16/03 4:51 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: DS</span><hr size=1> There is aggro associated with the actual casting of the ds btw.  At least on the druid version, if you ds someone that's engaged with a mob you will get aggro on yourself.  It's not a lot but its usually best to ds your tank before the pull.<br>
<br>
