<br>
Where I found flickering flame to be imensely usefull was when I couldnt land a nuke on the mobs my group was fighting. I went into LGuk for example at 29. Nothing would land on the mobs, but I could DS the tanks and that damage all added up. <br>
<br>
Same thing in the dreadlands. For a long time I couldnt land spells on the bigger doggies. DS to the rescue. Drop it on the tank, and med for the duration. At least you are contributing something.<br>
<br>
So usefull. Yup, but situational.  It's good to have some kind of utility occasionally. <p><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=285527">Daareon Ravenstar</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> -  56 Outrider - <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Ayonae Ro</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
